                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Team Captain, Business Manager</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Senior</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Brendan started with the team as a sophomore in the team’s rookie year. He helped to create and manage the team’s social media accounts on Twitter, Instagram, and Facebook, and published a number of articles for newspapers. In the team’s second year, Brendan served as the co-chair of the Business Committee. As co-chair, he organized the team’s media efforts, managed its fundraising goals, applied for grants, and spoke with potential sponsors. This year, Brendan will be serving as Business Manager and as a team captain. In his free time, Brendan can be found rowing on Duxbury Bay. He has rowed for four years, and serves as a captain for the high school crew team. Brendan serves as co-chair for Duxbury High School’s Principal’s Advisory, and is a member of the National Honor Society. Brendan plays the tuba and trombone. The earlier of which he plays in Duxbury High School’s Wind Ensemble. Brendan also serves as a L.I.N.K. Leader at DHS, helping to welcome incoming freshmen. Brendan is an active advocate for STEM education and cross-disciplinary educational programs.
</p>
